      "seed": 546036929,
      "version": 688,
      "versionNonce": 1457635215,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777597172615,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Flow engineering and Finite state machine\n\nLangGraph is a low level orchestration framework for building stateful multi-agent applications. \nIt helps with creating workflows where each step processes the data and hands over to the next step.\n\nThere concepts that are core to LangGraph are:\n1. State: Shared Memory that all nodes can read and write from\n2. Node: Functions that perform specific tasks (such as process data)\n3: Edges: Connection between nodes that define the flow\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Flow engineering and Finite state machine\n\nLangGraph is a low level orchestration framework for building stateful multi-agent applications. \nIt helps with creating workflows where each step processes the data and hands over to the next step.\n\nThere concepts that are core to LangGraph are:\n1. State: Shared Memory that all nodes can read and write from\n2. Node: Functions that perform specific tasks (such as process data)\n3: Edges: Connection between nodes that define the flow\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
